description.p:
The present invention relates to a method for the production of a silicon feedstock, the silicon feedstock being for producing directionally solidified Czrochralski, float zone or multicrystalline silicon ingots, thin silicon sheets or ribbons for the production of silicon wafers for PV solar cells which method is characterized in that metallurgical grade silicon produced in an electric arc furnace by carbothermic reduction furnace and containing up to 300 ppma boron and up to 100 ppma phosphorus is subjected to the following refining steps:
a) treatment of the metallurgical grade silicon with a calcium-silicate slag to reduce the boron content of the silicon to between 0.3 and 5.0 ppma;
b) solidifying the slag treated silicon from step a);
c) leaching the silicon from step b) in at least one leaching step by an acid leach solution to remove impurities;
d) melting the silicon from step c);
e) solidifying the molten silicon from step d) in the form of an ingot by directional solidification ;
f) removing the upper part of the solidified ingot from step e) to provide a silicon ingot containing 0.3 to 5.0 ppma boron, 0.5 to 3.5 ppma phosphorus and less than 150 ppma of metallic elements and less than 100 ppma carbon distributed in the material;
g) crushing and/or sizing the silicon from step f).

claim.claim-text:
Verfahren zur Herstellung eines Silicium-Rohstoffs, wobei der Silicium-Rohstoff zum Herstellen von gerichtet erstarrten Czochralski, Floatzone oder multikristallinen Silicium-Ingots, dünnen Siliciumbögen oder -bändern für die Herstellung von Silicium-Wafern für PV-Solarzellen ist, dadurch gekennzeichnet, dass metallurgisches Silicium, hergestellt in einem Elektrolichtbogenofen durch karbothermischen Reduktionsofen und bis zu 300 ppma Bor und bis zu 100 ppma Phosphor enthaltend, den folgenden Raffinationsschritten unterworfen wird:
a) Behandlung des metallurgischen Siliciums mit einer Calciumsilicat-Schlacke, um den Borgehalt des Siliciums auf zwischen 0,3 und 5,0 ppma zu verringern;
b) Verfestigen des mit Schlacke behandelten Siliciums von Schritt a);
c) Auslaugen des Siliciums von Schritt b) in mindestens einem Auslaugeschritt durch eine Säureauslaugungslösung, um Verunreinigungen zu entfernen;
d) Schmelzen des Siliciums von Schritt c);
e) Verfestigen des geschmolzenen Siliciums von Schritt d) in Form eines Ingots durch gerichtete Erstarrung;
f) Entfernen des oberen Teils des erstarrten Ingots von Schritt e), um einen Silicium-Ingot vorzusehen, welcher 0,3 bis 5,0 ppma Bor und 0,5 bis 3,5 ppma Phosphor, weniger als 150 ppma metallische Elemente und weniger als 100 ppma Kohlenstoff im Material verteilt enthält;
g) Zerstoßen und/oder Klassieren des Siliciums von Schritt f).

A method for the production of a silicon feedstock, the silicon feedstock being for producing directionally solidified Czochralski, float zone or multicrystalline silicon ingots, thin silicon sheets or ribbons for the production of silicon wafers for PV solar cells, characterised in that metallurgical grade silicon produced in an electric arc furnace by carbothermic reduction furnace and containing up to 300 ppma boron and up to 100 ppma phosphorus is subjected to the following refining steps:
a) treatment of the metallurgical grade silicon with a calcium-silicate slag to reduce the boron content of the silicon to between 0.3 and 5.0 ppma;
b) solidifying the slag treated silicon from the step a);
c) leaching the silicon from step b) in at least one leaching step by an acid leach solution to remove impurities;
d) melting the silicon from step c);
e) solidifying the molten silicon from step d) in the form of an ingot by directional solidification;
f) removing the upper part of the solidified ingot from step e) to provide a silicon ingot containing 0.3 to 5.0 ppma boron and 0.5 to 3.5 ppma phosphorus, less than 150ppma of metallic elements and less than 100 ppma carbon distributed in the material;
g) crushing and/or sizing the silicon from step f).
